c: 12
v: 80
t: "So, when they lost hope of moving him, they withdrew to take counsel among themselves. The eldest of them said: \"Do you not know how your father took a solemn pledge from you in God’s Name, and how, before that, you failed with regard to Joseph? Never will I depart from this land, until my father gives me leave, or God judges for me (by ending my life or enabling me to win back my brother). And He is the Best of judges"